<Font size="+2"><font face="Book Antiqua">
<P>The Prince Rupert City and Regional Archives 
  was established in 1980. The mandate is to acquire and preserve 
  records and documents related to the history and culture of Prince Rupert, 
  Port Edward, Port Essington, Port Simpson, Anyox, and the surrounding area.<BR>
  <BR>
  The Archives holdings consist of photographs and negatives, manuscripts such as
  minutes, financial records, letters and diaries, maps, newspapers, sound recordings, and historical reference material. </p>
</CENTER>
</font> <BR>

<p><Center><font face="Book Antiqua" size="+3">The book <em>Prince Rupert: An Illustrated History </em>is now available</em> <BR>
$39.95 plus shipping and handling </center>
</p> 
